Jul 6 2009 	Old classic but luxurious and dependable as ever	I stayed here for 4 nights in June and got an excellent rate via the British Airways website. I first stayed at the Peninsula Palace Hotel about 9 years ago and have been back many times. Despite the huge growth in number of international 5-star hotels in Beijing, this grand hotel is still one of the very best. I cannot understand why this hotel is not ranked in the top 3 in Beijing. The service here is as impeccable as ever. Staff in the restaurant at breakfast are attentive and efficient. The buffet breakfast is excellent with many choices. The rooms are very comfortable, although without an expansive view (as most rooms will look into a neighbouring office building). The Chinese restaurant in the hotel is one of the best in the city. The location of the Peninsula cannot be beaten, a few minutes from the department stores on Wangfujiang and a few minutes away by taxi from the Forbidden City. There is a supermarket around the corner for snacks and bottled drinks if you do not want to use the more expensive minibar in the room. Across the road are 2 other newer hotels i.e. the Regent and the Legendale. Both of these hotels look good although I cannot make a comparison as I have not stayed at either. The Peninsula is an excellent choice and a safe bet for those who want a comfortable hotel with proven great service in an excellent location. There is a high end mall (e.g. Chanel, Gucci etc) in the basement levels of the hotel although this is usually empty of shoppers. Note - as the hotel is located in an area of 5-star hotels, and therefore abound with &quot;wealthy travellers&quot; by Chinese standards, you are likely to be approached by young women offering &quot;massage services&quot; if you go walking in the evening. Pretty harmless but worth being aware of. I would definitely recommend this hotel and will come back here again, despite the competition.	
