Apr 20 2009 	Great time while there but then there was afterward...	Booked a winter special package for an overnight stay in mid-December. I had to fly in and out of Beijing for just one night for a business-related event, and loved the service. For CNY 1300, I had a standard room, plus free breakfast, and a round-trip (not one-way, but round-trip) airport transfer in one of their new BMW 7-Series. The had a large sign with the person in a hotel uniform waiting for me at the airport, who took my bags and called down for the car to pull around. After a short ride, upon pulling into the hotel there was a full staff of people standing outside (in the December cold) for my arrival. One to open the car door, one for my bags, one to open the hotel door, and one who was taking me straight to my room to check-in(no front desk). Once in my room, I relaxed, went down to the pool while having my clothes/shoes prepped for the evening, and enjoyed taking a swim. The pool attendant laid out towels for me, brought bottled water, but would walk along side of the pool with me as I was swimming laps, a little strange having a stranger watch me swim back and forth. Came back and with my evening attire ready and laid out in the room, went off for the evening to my event. The next day, woke up and went to breakfast (also included) and was wowed by the selection and quality of the offerings, I was thoroughly pleased and stuffed. Same car service upon departure to the airport. Those who know Beijing (I used to live there, now in Shanghai) know that a taxi from Wangfujing area to the airport can be about 100 yuan, so with RT limo service saved 200 Yuan i would have otherwise been forced to spend. (Found out afterward that their standard fee for limo service is usually CNY800 one-way) Plus free breakfast, free internet, free pressing and shoe shine, I felt like it was a steal for what I paid, and the service was nice the whole time. Two complaints though (one small, the other big), first is that the room was on the small side, I really felt it could have been a bit bigger, but it was tastefully decorated and relatively modern (with 42-inch plasma). When walking into the room it was kind-of like a &quot;this is it?&quot; reaction. Second was their billing. I gave them my credit card for the room guarantee, but paid cash. Usually a guarantee (at least in my experience) is used for minibar charges when you leave or if something is un-settled and you are gone. The evening after I had left, I found out they had charged my credit card for the room (plus extra), even though my bill was paid in full, in cash, upon departure, and I had to wait 2 weeks for them to take the charge off. Was un-happy when I learned this, especially since my credit card was charged more than what my actual bill was (by almost US$100). Was embarrassing when I went to use this card and told that I didn't have enough balance (and I couldn't think of anything at all i actually purchased with it), and upon logging into my account see a charge on my card for Peninsula Beijing, when I'm holding the bill that says paid in full, in cash. Kind-of ruined my great feeling I had when I left the hotel. The hotel itself was a very nice experience, but I still don't understand their billing office.	
