 should never be accepted. The public disparaging remarks of these two managers were both unacceptable and made some of us patrons and guests uncomfortable. Upon the second manager pulling this action, we approached the manager and politely informed him that their actions were creating an unpleasant atmosphere for us. The manager responded, &quot;Thank you for your input. If there is anything other input we need from you, we'll let you know..&quot; It was both aloof and terse and quite insulting. For the standard that the Peninsula is supposed to exhibit, it falls very short. If any of you see the caucasian chef or hotel managers berating the staff in public, hope you all can speak your mind to them as well.	
